New Computer Science Course: Game Theory and Design
Target Audience
This course would be for 11th or 12th graders who have taken a computer science class before
Where does it fit
This could either be run as a Saturday elective course or a one semester elective. Students would receive 1 math elective credit.
Student must have taken either python, AP CSP or AP CSA.
General description
This course will teach students the fundamental elements of basic game design. By the end of this course, students will have a better 
understanding of the process of game design, have more knowledge about game design related careers, and will be able to create their own game.
